OS requirements
===============
1) All major OS platfrorm are supported
    a) windows -- 10 or 7
    b) Mac OS
    c) Linux -- any recent release is fine.

Java requirements
=================
1) Java 11 or higher required
2) openJDK required

IDE requirements
===================
IntelliJ

Downloaded a maven Binary for version 3.3 + 
==> https://mirrors.estointernet.in/apache/maven/maven-3/3.6.3/binaries/apache-maven-3.6.3-bin.zip

extract the zip file in current location 
==> /c/Users/Sagar/projects/Maven_project

Then add the path to it in system variables for windows PATH variable. Below is the path
==> /c/Users/Sagar/projects/Maven_project/apache-maven-3.6.3/bin

Then you can check the version of maven using below command
==> mvn --version

Maven installation on Linux
===========================

1) for this we are going to make use of tomcat.local VM running on VMware 
2) we can check the status of jdk and java version using below command
    java --version

    openjdk 11.0.7 2020-04-14 LTS
    OpenJDK Runtime Environment Corretto-11.0.7.10.1 (build 11.0.7+10-LTS)
    OpenJDK 64-Bit Server VM Corretto-11.0.7.10.1 (build 11.0.7+10-LTS, mixed mode)
3) Also we can check the java home set using
    echo $JAVA_HOME
4) then we can download the maven binary from below link
    https://mirrors.estointernet.in/apache/maven/maven-3/3.6.3/binaries/apache-maven-3.6.3-bin.zip
5) After downloading the binary from above link unzip the file in /tmp
    unzip /tmp/apache-maven-3.6.3-bin.zip
6) Then mv the /tmp/apache-maven-3.6.3 to /opt
7) then ad the path to maven bin to PATH environment variable using below command
    export PATH=/opt/apache-maven-3.6.3/bin:$PATH
8) Then we can check the maven version installed using below command
    mvn --version.